ActionNetwork

ActionNetwork can do a lot, but it's user interface is awful. It's very difficult to find something, even if you somehow managed to find it before, so here is a cheatsheet of page links:

Page for a User to Sign Up

https://actionnetwork.org/forms/southeastern-massachusetts-coalition-for-a-free-palestine-member-map

https://tiny.cc/sema-activist (shortened URL)

Log On to ActionNetwork

https://actionnetwork.org/

Work with Southeastern Massachusetts Coalition for a Free Palestine

Edit the User Form

https://actionnetwork.org/forms/southeastern-massachusetts-coalition-for-a-free-palestine-member-map/edit

Modify General Notification Email

https://actionnetwork.org/groups/south-eastern-massachusetts-coalition-for-a-free-palestine/manage#tab_settings

Modify Response Form Message and Form Notification Email

https://actionnetwork.org/forms/southeastern-massachusetts-coalition-for-a-free-palestine-member-map/manage#tab_response

View Results and Download CSV

https://actionnetwork.org/reports/all-activists-46317/manage?activist_download=1

If the generation date is old, click "Generate," wait a bit, refresh your screen and the date of the available download should match the current time and date. Downloading will give you a comma-delimited file easily readable in most spreadsheets:

Maintenance

Not normally recommended, but if you need to delete someone from ActionNetwork you must unsubscribe them from Southeastern Massachusetts Coalition for a Free Palestine.

ActionNetwork assumes they are subscribed elsewhere so there's no actual "delete" capability. But we can remove people from our list. To accomplish this: click on the person's email address in the Results page above. This takes you to the details of the person's interactions with us. On the left you will find an option to unsubscribe from the SEMA mailing list. When you return to the Results page, at the bottom you'll find a "Refresh" button. This will update the page. Wait a bit and the page will no longer display people you've unsubscribed.
